keyDayCopy: China alerts the WHO that it has identified a new coronavirus. Although there had been several cases of pneumonia in December and possibly November in Wuhan, this was the moment that the world's attention was drawn to the mysterious disease.
Chinese scientists sequence the disease, and identify three strains.
The virus claims its first fatality, as China would announce two days later.
Wuhan placed under lockdown. WHO notes increasing evidence for human-to-human transmission.
The disease gets a name: Covid-19
The disease has now entered Africa. First death in France.
Italy has three fatalities, and starts to cancel events.
Lombardy, Italy's worst affected region, goes into lockdown. Iran is badly affected.
The WHO declares the disease a pandemic.
Spain has 100 deaths in a single day. Much worse is still to come.
US Congress passes a $2tn emergency programme.
Boris Johnson, UK PM, tests positive.
The disease now has 1m confirmed cases worldwide.
It seems likely that when the data is compiled for the hundredth day, 100k people will have been killed by the disease. CHECK CHECK
